result.name: Blooming Restaurant

reviews.text: Excellent food with heart-felt quality! Highly recommend to those who have high expectation on food quality.

Have always walked by and wanted to try it. Didn't blow my mind, but good food with great service -- almost felt like eating at someone's house with homestyle hospitality. (Granted, we and another table were the only customers for most of our meal.) Downstairs is a small but comfortable dining space. Not sure about upstairs. The dishes were not over-seasoned, or too salty or oily, like most Chinese restaurants. Generous portions at decent prices. They do charge a per-person tea fee, but it included a welcome snack: spicy tofu + bean sprouts.
I had many meals there, every dishes were good. Their hot and spice dishes particular addictive. I stop by lunch, I stop by dinner. It became my dining room.
Superb food and service - a special experience.
Good food and good service.
